  "prompt": "Are there international laws against money laundering?",
  "response": "Yes, there are several international laws and agreements aimed at preventing money laundering:\n\n1. The Financial Action Task Force (FATF)\n- An intergovernmental organization that sets global standards\n- Develops recommendations for combating money laundering and terrorist financing\n\n2. United Nations Conventions\n- UN Convention Against Transnational Organized Crime\n- UN Convention Against Corruption\n\n3. Basel Committee on Banking Supervision\n- Provides guidelines for banking regulations and anti-money laundering practices\n\n4. International Monetary Fund (IMF) guidelines\n- Helps countries develop anti-money laundering frameworks\n\n5. European Union Anti-Money Laundering Directives\n- Establish regulatory requirements for financial institutions in EU countries\n\nMost countries have domestic laws implementing these international standards, requiring financial institutions to:\n- Verify customer identities\n- Report suspicious transactions\n- Maintain transaction records\n- Implement compliance programs\n\nThese laws require financial institutions to monitor and report potentially illegal financial activities to help prevent money laundering, terrorist financing, and other financial crimes.",
